== Ethical and Compliance Considerations

Adversarial testing in this work is bounded to authorized environments and framed as defensive research. This constraint is not procedural formality; it is required to ensure legal proportionality and organizational accountability when testing potentially harmful behaviors.

Method execution is aligned with secure SDLC and governance expectations from NIST and EU regulatory contexts @nist_sp800_218_2022 @eu_nis2_2022 @eu_dora_2022 @eu_ai_act_2024.

Operationally, this implies four guardrails for all experiments: documented authorization scope, data minimization during logging, controlled handling of sensitive outputs, and auditable retention policies for test artifacts. These guardrails ensure that methodological rigor and compliance obligations are treated as coupled requirements rather than separate tracks.
